Subject: [PATCH] feat(news): L1-L6 layers on persistent-bottleneck panel +
 ABB/AMKR + 2x cards
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Patch 0085 closes the gaps you flagged on the Persistent Bottleneck Reading
panel and Transformational Contracts list:

1. PERSISTENT BOTTLENECK PANEL — new L1-L6 block per card
   The architectural-adaptation block grouped beneficiaries by causal pattern
   (POWER_EFFICIENCY / ALT_ACCELERATOR / ...) which made AKAM (edge),
   Sterlite-type names (industrial pass-through), AMD/INTC/ARM (CPU + sub),
   and ABB / AMKR feel missing on cards like HBM/DRAM and GRID/TRANSFORMERS.

   Now every persistent bottleneck card also renders the canonical 6-layer
   pricing-power transmission stack:
     L1 Direct Scarcity Capture     - TSM/MU/ASML/AMAT/KLAC/GEV/ABB/AMKR
     L2 Compute Substitutes         - AMD/INTC/ARM/QCOM/AVGO/MRVL
     L3 Edge Distribution           - AKAM/NET/CIEN/LITE/COHR
     L4 Transmission Winners        - STL/PRY/GLW/Murata/Ibiden/Shinko
     L5 Platform Beneficiaries      - MSFT/AMZN/GOOGL/META/ORCL
     L6 Infrastructure / Efficiency - VRT/JCI/CARR/Delta/nVent

   Mandatory injects render with amber star + amber border so 'AKAM is
   mandatory on INTERCONNECT' is visually unambiguous. T0->T4 transmission
   cascade is rendered below the layers.

2. ROSTER ADDITIONS
   - ABB (ABBNY) added to L1; mandatory on ENERGY_INFRA + COOLING_INFRA
     alongside ETN, SBGSY, GEV, SMNEY, HTHIY.
   - AMKR (Amkor) added to L1; mandatory on PACKAGING_INFRA alongside
     TSM, AMAT, KLAC.

3. 2x CARD SIZES
   Persistent Bottleneck cards: title 11->17, sub 10->14, meta 10->13,
   top-signal 9->12, ticker chips 9->13, rationale 8->11, losers 8->11,
   adaptation header 9->14, padding 8/10->14/18, grid minWidth 280->440.

   Transformational Contracts cards: title 11->16, value$ 9->14, ticker
   chip 9->13, counterparty 9->13, padding 8/10->14/18, minWidth 360->520.

   Section headers: 10 -> 15.

Cache key bumped v30 -> v31.
